DUBAI, United Arab Emirates (AP) — Allrounder Sharafuddin Ashraf replaced Asghar Afghan in the Afghanistan squad at the T20 World Cup on Tuesday.Sharafuddin was approved as a replacement “following concerns over Asghar’s mental wellbeing,” the International Cricket Council said in a statement.Asghar retired from all forms of international cricket after Afghanistan beat Namibia on Sunday. Afghanistan, in semifinals contention, still has two group games left, including against India on Wednesday.The 26-year-old Sharafuddin bowls left-arm spin and bats right-handed.___More AP sports: https://apnews.com/hub/apf-sports and https://twitter.com/AP_Sports